{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ae60fac4-f3e5-4088-a3fa-6749aa2301d1","content":"Here are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core** (`dotnet new webapi`)\n- `--auth Individual` – ASP.NET Identity with local accounts\n- `--auth IndividualB2C` – Azure AD B2C\n- `--auth SingleOrg` – Azure AD (single tenant)\n- `--auth MultiOrg` – Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n- `--auth Windows` – Windows/Negotiate auth\n\n**Node.js** – Express/Fastify + middleware:\n- Passport.js (local, OAuth, JWT, etc.)\n- `express-jwt` / `jsonwebtoken` for JWT-based auth\n\n**Python** – FastAPI / Django REST Framework:\n- FastAPI: OAuth2 with `python-jose`, `passlib`\n- Django: `djangorestframework-simplejwt`, session auth, token auth\n\n**Recommended starting point** for .NET:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nFor Node.js:\n```bash\nnpx express-generator myapi   # then add passport/jwt\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific stack and auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8d942851-fae8-494d-920b-ff62a6010f82","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular frameworks.","outputTokens":342},"id":"4d2208aa-3e97-4f51-914b-bbaebd7c78d9","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:48:22.385Z","parentId":"02f39025-eaf4-45ff-8977-8fd2ec13d852"}
